```julia
function timezone_bumper(dt::DateTime, bump::Integer = 3)
    return DateTime(yearmonthday(dt), hour(dt) + bump, minute(dt), second(dt))
end
```

This function takes a `DateTime` object and an integer representing the number of hours to add (`bump`). It defaults to adding three hours if no explicit value is provided for `bump`. The function works by creating a new `DateTime` with the specified time zone adjustment, ensuring that only valid types are accepted.
